ClytiaThe Chrysanthemum Peruvianum, or, to employ a better-known
term, the turnsolwhich turns continually towards the sun, covers itself, like
Peru, the country from which it comes, with dewy clouds which cool and
refresh
its flowers during the most violent heat of the day.
