The Humanitarians held that God was to be understood as having really
a human form.
Vide Clarke's Sermons
, vol.1, page 26, fol.edit.
The drift of Milton's argument, leads him to employ language which would
appear, at first sight, to verge upon their doctrine; but it will be seen
immediately
,
that he guards himself against the charge of having adopted one of
the most ignorant errors of the dark ages of the church.
Dr. Sumner's Notes
on Milton's Christian Doctrine
.
This opinion, in spite of many testimonies to the contrary, could never have
been very general. Andeus, a Syrian of Mesopotamia, was condemned for
the opinion, as heretical. He lived in the beginning of the fourth century.
His disciples were called Anthropmorphites.
Vide Du Pin
.
